0 GUILD 'THE GUILD'~
		     
		    `KT`whe`WGu`wil`Kd`w		

        Since the dawn of time there have been special men and 
women of all races. While there are those that are interested 
in power, prestige, wealth or even some fanatical goal, there 
have been those individuals who are only interested in one 
thing - Adventure. They are the ones who who are shunned by 
most as crazy, called glory seekers by the envious, and 
lamented by those who have achived status as tossing their 
lives away. But the call to adventure is too strong to resist 
for these poeple.
        They are the ones who arrive into town durring the
middle of the night, weary from their journey, traveling cloak 
covered in mud and stained with blood. They try to pay for 
their single drink with coins no one has ever seen before, 
belonging to a long dead kingdom. Hidden in a worn leather 
pouch at their side is the lost artifact of Kaldin the mage.
        The affairs of kings and men interest these people 
little, unless they broaden their range of knowledge, bring them
in contact with lost articles of power, or the pay is right. 
The politics matter not, it is the adventure and the fight that 
such conflict brings that would draw true adventurers to it 
like a moth to a flame. 
        The guild however as a whole cares not for such petty 
things, usualy it is only the individual members who get 
involved in such things. It takes a great catastropy or 
overwhelming need for the highest memebers of the guild to 
call a council and order the whole guild into action. Even 
then the guilds history is potmarked with times when action 
should have been taken and none was, when action was not 
warrented but given, and even descisions that almost tore the
guild apart as some memebers stood on one side of an issue and
other members on the the other side. In recent years the current 
council has taken to avoid action unless absolutly nessicary.
        Adventurers however have always been on the outside of 
most regular society, being too roudy to fit into high 
society, being too free willed to join a most groups, but 
always seeming to gravitate towards others of a like mind. 
It was from this desire the Guild was formed. No one is sure
who formed the guild or really when, it has been around for as 
long as anyone can remember. Everytime one of the members 
thinks they've nailed down the founders another obscure 
reference to it pops up in some even more ancient tomb.
The guild just keeps on going from generation to generation, 
it has never been wiped out, and even on the rare occasions 
when all the members have been slain or disapeared it was only 
a matter of time befor new adveturers rose up and took the 
mantel and the guild continued.
        People from all walks of life and of all races hear 
the call of Adventure. The guild cares not for what one did or 
does befor joining, and even after joining the guild usualy 
does not care what it's members do. Though most are too 
wrapped up in their own quest for adventure and knowledge to 
cause many problems with the world at large. 
        Their members inclued many as many professions 
naturaly lead one on to the path of adventure. Warriors lust
for battle, to search out stronger and more powerfull foes, take
them to the brink of civilization and further. Thieves desire
for richs can cause them the decend into the very pits of hell
for items that will fetch a kings ransom many times over. Clerics
holy crusades take them all over the the known world and beyond
in the name of their God. Mages quest for knowledge can lead them
into areas that haven't been seen for millenia just for the 
possibilty of a little more arcane knowledge.
        There is only one requirement to get into the Guild, 
prove one's worthyness and lust for adventure. New members are 
constantly scowering the land in search of lost artifacts and 
lore to prove they have what it takes to truely call themselves
an Adventurer! But even after joining many adventurers continue 
their travels, always trying to one up each other and themselves.
For an adventurer only craves one thing in the end, the thrill
of the quest and a good companion to share their trials with.        

The current leader in title only is Giaij.
~

0 NIGHTFALL~

The `BNightfall`w clan was formed relatively recently.

A band of outlaws, mostly murders, outcast and forced to live in the
forests and other remote areas of the world, the members of `BNightfall`w
are known for random killing, terrorism, and other acts of violence.

Though all members aren't inherently evil, `RPK`w is required, for members
have been known to lend assistance and heal others, then kill them when
they least suspect it.

The only requirements for joining `BNightfall`w are to be above level 20
and a player killer.

