0 ROSE 'BLACK ROSE'~
The Clan of the `KBlack Rose`w:

The `KBlack Rose`w was founded many centuries ago, during a brief period
of violence. The founder, a High Priest of Rahl, gathered as many as he
could together and told them of a dream he had the previous night...

"The Master came before me last night. 'My Master,' I said, 'what can thy
humble servant do for thee?'

"He spoke without speaking, 'I know the state of this world, and I say to
thee that if you take up arms, you, too shall perish. If you embrace those
ideals that you preach, I shall protect you.'

"'My Master,' I said, 'I shall do as you wish.' but, even as I said this,
He had gone.

"Come, my friends. We must kneel and pray for His protection. All ye who
would fight, leave us now, for ye are dead men either way."

One month later, lookouts on the city walls reported armies cresting the
nearbly hills. Crowds of people flocked to the walls, trying to get a view
of the approaching masses. The leaders of the armies approached the city
walls and demanded the city's surrender. When the king, his faith
unshaken, refused, the leaders turned to their armies and odered them to
attack. When the lead element of the attacking force got within 100 feet
of the walls, there was a thunderous roar, combined with the screams of
thousands, as they were mysteriously cut down. The leaders of the
attacking armies, realizing that there was no way that they could win,
knelt and surrendered. 

Later, a group of people, using the High Priest as spiritual guidance,
formed what is now known as the `KBlack Rose`w.

The only requirement to join the `KBlack Rose`w is to be above level 10.

The Patron god of the clan is Rahl and the current High Priest is Xanth.
~


91 JOBS~
This is a partial list of what a god of any given level should be doing. It is
not complete yet.


Heroes:
You should be helping mortals in minor ways (i.e. not handing out free spells
right and left).  An ideal example is leading quest parties or missions to 
get corpses...don't just get the corpse for a person, make them come along and
help you do it.

Angels:
Angels and higher level gods may not assist mortals directly in any way.  
An Angel's main job is to help with quests (via switch), or possibly run
small quest of their own -- but the rewards should be minimal.

Deities:
Deities have two main roles: reimbursement and quest running.  Be skeptical
on reimburses, don't just hand out every piece of gear.  I suggest limiting
reimbursements to 10 items at a time, and make sure that you do not load things
at too high a level (new format items have hard-coded levels, so are not a
problem).  vnum and stat are useful for this.  You can draft Angels to help you
run a quest, and please note that quests should NOT have huge rewards -- the
main point should be to have fun.  Deities have no business trying to enforce
rules -- the most you should do to a player is a NOCHANNEL or similar light
punishment.

Gods:
Gods can run quests just like Deities, and it's nice to do reimbursements too.
However, the main role of a God is keeping the peace.  Gods can enforce (but
not create rules), using the various NOTELL-class commands, as well as deny,
purge, freeze, and ban (but be careful with these commands!)  Gods are expected
to help make the mud run more smoothly, power trips are strictly verbotten.

Not fufilling the roles of your office can result in demotion or deletion.
~


