-1 RULES~
These are the rules of Broken Shadows.  For other matters, use commom
sense (if that fails, ask).

* foul language will not be tolerated from anyone (including gods) on 
  public channels. Punishments range from deletion to NOCHANNELing.

* sexual harassment of any form will not be tolerated, punishable by deletion
  or site bans.

* your presence here is a privilige not a right <--- please note this! 
  Broken Shadows is private property, not a public service. Your privelige
  to connect at any given time is not guaranteed. This means that we do not 
  necessarily have to have a reason to deny you access or delete your
  characters.
 
* no multiple logins, multiple playing, or helping your own characters with 
  other characters you own -- by any arrangment. You may have multile 
  characters, but if both are on at the same time, they may both be deleted.
  Tintin, etc. robots will not be tolerated. Your character will be
  disconnected and/or deleted.
 
* Rules may be ammended/changed at any point and may be done without warning, 
  notice, or even evidence of sanity. You are also responisble for rules
  posted in notes or spoken by an immortal until you hear
  differently.

* no kill stealing.  This means you cannot attack a mob someone else is 
  fighting, unless they ask you to. Also avoid attacking fleeing mobs. We 
  realize that accidents do happen, but multiple "accidents" are suspicious.
  This includes attacking a mob and fleeing so that another player may
  kill it, as well as casting certain spells, like curse and weaken
  on it.

* cheating will not be tolerated.  This includes accepting favors from gods
  and exploiting bugs. If you find a bug, report it, then do not use it.

* if you are asked by an immortal to refrain from doing something and you 
  fail to comply, you may suffer a penalty. Penalties may be anything that
  the immortal sees fit.

* Summoning/pushing players to aggressive mobs or vice versa will not be
  tolerated.

* Spamming non-combat related commands, regardless of whether an immortal
  is on, is rude. Those found doing it will be punished.

* problems with rules may be brought to Rahl and no one else, even if they
  were spoken/posted by another immortal.
~



