0 DELETE~
Use the delete command to erase unwanted characters, so the name will be
available for use.  This command must be typed twice to delete a character,
and you cannot be forced to delete.  Typing delete with an argument will
return your character to 'safe' status if you change your mind after the
first delete.
~

0 HEALER~
The healer decided to grab a quick buck, and now charges for his heals.  Some
services are still free to players of level 10 or below, however.  To see
a full listing of the healer's services, type 'heal' at his residence. To
receive healing, bring plenty of money, and type 'heal spell'.
~ 

-1 TAX TAXES~
Broken Shadows charges a tax on the wealthiest players, to help pay for
all the sub issue equipment and guard death benefits.  This tax amounts to
50% of all gold above 10,000 coins, each and every time you log on.

There is also a surcharge on your bank accounts, which amounts to 25% of
all gold above 50,000 coins each and every time you log on.
~

-1 GAIN~
The gain command is used to learn new skills, once the proper trainer has 
been found.  The following options can be used with gain:

gain list:    list all groups and skills that can be learned
gain points:  lower your creation points by 1 (costs two sessions)
gain <name>:  add a skill or skill group, at the listed cost
gain convert: turns 10 practices into one training session

Gain uses training sessions, not practices. (see 'help train')
Gained skills and groups do NOT increase your experience per level or total
number of creation points. 
~

0 SKILLS SPELLS~
The skills and spells commands are used to display your character's list
of available skills (or spells, as the case may be).  They are listed in
order of level, with mana cost (for spells) or percentage (for skills)
listed where applicable.
~


0 OUTFIT~
The outfit command, usable by levels 5 and below, equips your character with
a new set of sub issue gear (banner, weapon, helmet, shield, and vest), 
courtesy of the Mayor's warehouses.  Only empty equipment slots are affected.
~

0 AUTO AUTOLIST AUTOLOOT AUTOGOLD AUTOSAC AUTOEXIT AUTOASSIST AUTOSPLIT~
Broken Shadows uses varies automatic actions, to ease the boredom of
always splitting gold and sacrificing corpses.  The commands are as
follows:

autolist  : list all automatic actions
autoloot  : take all equipment from dead mobiles
autogold  : take all gold from dead mobiles
autosac   : sacrifice dead monsters (if autoloot is on, only empty corpes)
autoexit  : display room exits upon entering a room
autosplit : split up spoils from combat among your group members
autoassit : makes you help group members in combat
autodamage: lets you see the amount of damage you do per hit in a fight

Typing a command sets the action (except for autolist), typing it again removes
it. 
~ 

-1 COUNT~
The count command displays the number of people (that you can see) logged
into the mud.  It also displays the highest number observed that day, if
it is higher.
~ 
 
-1 CHANGES~
To see a list of changes, type 'CHANGES'.
~

-1 GATE~
The gate spell is a powerful transportation magic that opens up a portal 
between your character and another person or creature somewhere else in the
world.  This portal will transport you and any pet you might have, but not
other members of your group.  Monsters recieve a save against gate, and
monster or players more than 3 levels higher than you can not be gated to at 
all.  God rooms, private rooms, and no recall rooms cannot be gated to, and
no recall rooms cannot be gated out of.  Finally, any god or hero is also 
immune to gate, as well as in player who has no summon set.
~

92 CRITERIA~
The Immortal Criteria 

Immortal players should realize that their immortal powers are a privilege
and not a right. The decisions of the imps are final, and will be
respected, for they are the true law of the land.

The advancement of immortals is a very specific and complicated matter.
Immortals do not recieve expierience points, therfore they are evaluated
by expierience and skills aquired by doing tasks required of them. These
tasks include building, law enforcement, and coding. Also taken into
consideration the actions off the immortal staff. Immortals are required
to abide by the ruls of the mud, and by the specific immortal rules stated
in help commandments/help jobs.

Level advancement criteria:

The immortal staff's main objective is to make the mud a better place for
the players. Immortals have many responsibilities and must be constantly
working on them in order to remain part of the imm staff and to advance in
rank.

Some of the immortal responsibilities include:

Creating an area and being familiar with OLC
Knowing and abiding by the rules of the MUD
Helping mortals and responding to their concerns (to an extent)
Enforcing the rules of the MUD
Any other specific tasks assigned to you
You also must have attended immortal meetings (although exceptions may be
made on this one)

All this is necessary in order to be _considered_ for level advancement.
There are excptions for every rule though. In some cases a immortal may be
assigned tasks that are not on this list and those may also be considered
for level advancememnt.

Proposing for level advancement:

Once an immortal has aquired the criteria necessary for advancement, a
random group of 4 immortals will be chosen to vote for the advancement of
said persons. If the vote is resulted in a tie, Rahl will cast the
deciding vote.

After a immortal reaches level 95, they will be given specific duties that
will aid them in advancement to the higher levels. You must prove to the
implementors that you are capable of performing the tasks assigned before
advancement can be considered. In addition, you will only qualify for such
advancement if there is a need for someone of that level.

Along with advancement there is the posibility of demotion. If an immortal
is not completing his or her tasks or is abusing their immortal powers
they may loose levels or fired from the immortal staff. This is something
that will be decided among the implementors, and will also be brought
before to a comittee. The final decision will be made by a combination of
a vote and the final decision of the implementors. Under some
circunstances, the immortal may be demoted or fired immediately.
~

